  "text": [
    "<strong dir=\"rtl\">פִּינָּה</strong>, <strong dir=\"rtl\">פִּנָּה</strong> f. (b. h.;  <a dir=\"rtl\" class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Jastrow,_פָּנָה.1\" data-ref=\"Jastrow, פָּנָה 1\"><a dir=\"rtl\" class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Jastrow,_פָּנָה.1\" data-ref=\"Jastrow, פָּנָה 1\">פָּנָה</a>)</a> <b>1)</b> <i>turn, movement</i>.—Pl. <span dir=\"rtl\"><a dir=\"rtl\" class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Jastrow,_פִּיּוֹת.1\" data-ref=\"Jastrow, פִּיּוֹת 1\">פִּינּוֹת</a> (פּוֹנוֹת</span>). <a class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Yoma.58b.12\" data-ref=\"Yoma 58b:12\">Yoma 58ᵇ</a> <span dir=\"rtl\">כל פי׳ שאתה פונה וכ׳</span> (Ms. M. 2 <span dir=\"rtl\">פנות</span>; Ms. O. <a dir=\"rtl\" class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Jastrow,_פֶּתֶן ².1\" data-ref=\"Jastrow, פֶּתֶן ² 1\">פו׳</a>) all the turns you make (in the Temple) must be towards the right; <a class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Yoma.15b.4\" data-ref=\"Yoma 15b:4\">ib. 15ᵇ</a> (Ms. M. <a dir=\"rtl\" class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Jastrow,_פֶּתֶן ².1\" data-ref=\"Jastrow, פֶּתֶן ² 1\">פו׳</a>); <a class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Zevachim.62b.8\" data-ref=\"Zevachim 62b:8\">Zeb. 62ᵇ</a> (Ms. M. <a dir=\"rtl\" class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Jastrow,_פֶּתֶן ².1\" data-ref=\"Jastrow, פֶּתֶן ² 1\">פו׳</a>); <a class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Sotah.15b.14\" data-ref=\"Sotah 15b:14\">Sot. 15ᵇ</a> <a dir=\"rtl\" class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Jastrow,_פֶּתֶן ².1\" data-ref=\"Jastrow, פֶּתֶן ² 1\">פו׳</a>; <a class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Yalkut_Shimoni_on_Torah.446.3\" data-ref=\"Yalkut Shimoni on Torah 446:3\">Yalk. Lev. 446</a> <span dir=\"rtl\">פְּנִיּוֹת</span>; a. e.—[With the exception of Sot. l. c. our editions read <span dir=\"rtl\">פינות</span>]. <b>—2)</b> <i>corner</i>. <a class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Shemot_Rabbah.37.1\" data-ref=\"Shemot Rabbah 37:1\">Ex. R. s. 37</a>, beg. (ref. to <a class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Zechariah.10.4\" data-ref=\"Zechariah 10:4\">Zech. X, 4</a>) <span dir=\"rtl\">ממנו פ׳ זה וכ׳</span> ‘from him (Israel) the cornerstone is taken’, this refers to King David (with ref. to <a class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Psalms.18.22\" data-ref=\"Psalms 18:22\">Ps. XVIII, 22</a>). <a class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Avot_D'Rabbi_Natan.28.9\" data-ref=\"Avot D'Rabbi Natan 28:9\">Ab. d’R. N. ch. XXVIII</a> <span dir=\"rtl\">שלש מידות … אבן פ׳ וכ׳</span> there are three qualities of scholars, a hewn stone (seated in the wall), a corner stone &c.; <span dir=\"rtl\">אבן פ׳ שיש לו שתי פיות וכ׳</span> (one versed in Midrash and Halakhah) is a corner stone which has two faces only.—Pl. as ab. <a class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Mishnah_Middot.1.1\" data-ref=\"Mishnah Middot 1:1\">Midd. I, 1</a> <span dir=\"rtl\"><span dir=\"rtl\">על ארבע</span> (<span dir=\"rtl\">פִּינּוֹתֶיהָ</span>) <span dir=\"rtl\">פִּינּוֹתָיו</span></span> in its four corners. <a class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Eruvin.11a.13\" data-ref=\"Eruvin 11a:13\">Erub. 11ᵃ</a>, v. <a dir=\"rtl\" class=\"refLink\" href=\"/Jastrow,_פֵּאָה.1\" data-ref=\"Jastrow, פֵּאָה 1\">פֵּאָה</a>."
  ],
